examples.en: No sooner said than done.
I'd sooner die than give up.
I'd sooner go by plane than by train.
Come a little sooner, if you can.
I'd sooner go hungry than eat junk food.
Sooner or later, fashion comes full circle.
He would sooner die than face them.
No sooner had I got into the house than the phone rang.
No sooner thought upon than done.
We may finish sooner than you think.
Please excuse me for not calling sooner.
The sooner you finish your homework, the sooner you can go outside and play.
This was bound to happen sooner or later.
Cats and dogs will sooner be cater-cosins.
Everything may happen sooner than you think.
You're going to have to face him sooner or later.
Something like that was bound to happen sooner or later.
She's cool to the idea right now, but sooner or later she'll come round.
If only he had talked to her sooner!
Many have faulted her for not acting sooner.
The government blundered by not acting sooner.
You could be out sooner if you behave yourself.
The eggs will hatch sooner in warm, moist conditions.
We cut through the neighbor's yard to get home sooner.
The clocks go back next week, so it will seem dark sooner.
They would have married sooner, but they had to wait for her divorce.
Far sooner than anyone thought possible, the Russians exploded an atomic bomb.
I was called down by my supervisor for not catching the accounting error sooner.
School finishes at the end of the week, and the sooner the better as far as I'm concerned.
Extra doses of the hormone caused the animals' reproductive organs to develop sooner than usual.
